cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.PF, cs.OS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with resource allocation in cloud computing systems, which are distributed and parallel in nature. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a mechanism for resource allocation in cloud computing systems, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as cloud computing systems rely heavily on networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed mechanism in terms of resource utilization and job completion times. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is also relevant as the paper deals with resource allocation in the context of operating systems for cloud computing.
